{
  "stem": "13063.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Since I was five, six years old, music was always a part of my life.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Always.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And not only of my life, but the life of family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Music was a-- an integral feature of everyday life-- of everyday life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was not a day without music, either from the radio, or from the piano, or from singing, or from discussing music.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Not a day went by without it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I started to play the piano-- to study piano, really-- with a teacher at the age of eight.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This is also when I started to sing in a choir with a cant-- with a famous cantor of Cracow, Yossel Mandelbaum, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He just died three years ago, at the age of 93, 94, in Brooklyn, New York.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was the cantor in the Cypress Shul in Cracow.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Cypress, C-I-P-R-E-S-S.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "C-Y-P-R-E-S-S.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Cypress Shul on [INAUDIBLE] Street in Cracow.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was a very beautiful synagogue, and he was the only one who had a [HEBREW] and a [HEBREW], because he was a [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Yossel Mandelbaum [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I will never forget his davening, his fervor, his tremendous impact on the people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "When he was davening-- they-- for example, when he said [HEBREW], when he blessed the new moon, the synagogue was rocking with sobs from-- especially from the women's gallery.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I remember it so distinctly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There were such tremendous sobs, loud sobs-- from-- from the women's gallery and from people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Because he moved the people so tremendously.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he gave me the-- the path.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He showed me the path in [HEBREW], in the [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It means the emotional cantorate-- cantorate-- the emotional cantorial art.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "See, because there's-- there are two cantorial arts.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There's the emotional cantorial art, practiced by cantors most in Eastern Europe.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
